main event: A civilian reported observing a round object hovering near his house on August 29, 1967.
interesting points: The object was about the size of a small airplane and hovered close to the observer,The observer described the object as not being a known aircraft and ruled out small planes or helicopters,The object disappeared before suddenly shooting away,The observer stated he is a very good observer of objects in the sky,The case was reevaluated due to insufficient data as the observer's report was not returned in 60 days.
witness description: civilian, claims to be a very good observer of objects in the sky
